This was a mildly amusing film. I watched it because I like Vivica A. Fox and Chris Kattan. Fox had a nice role. She was great and Kattan was good in a smaller role. The film focused on themes of redemption. The theme was that we should get to know people of different backgrounds and not rush to prejudge people. The film takes place during Christmas but the film is more about relationships than Christmas. I recommend this film for fans of Fox. Chabert from Party of Five was adorable. Malambri from Step Up3D held the movie together and had great chemistry with Chabert. This film would be rated PG. This is a clean family film. I also recommend this for fans of family films.
